OL,3,CMayor blasts rail operators for
OL,4,Cweather 'chaos'
OL,6,F"People depend on these services every
OL,7,Fday, not just to get from A to B, but
OL,8,Fto keep their lives running smoothly.
OL,9,FWhen the system fails, it's more than
OL,10,Fan inconvenience."
OL,12,FMr Rotheram criticised Merseyrail and
OL,13,FNetwork Rail, which is responsible for
OL,14,Fthe upkeep of the track and signalling.
OL,16,FIt was clear, he added, that the
OL,17,F"robust winter plans" that were
OL,18,Fsupposedly in place had failed.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@RO]yD@AOUyD@UO]
